							<div>
								<h3>Pre Conference Information</h3>
							
								<h4>Registration</h4>
                                <br />
								<p><a href="https://gc-registration.iaea.org/">Registration</a> is open as of 31 July 2013 for designated representatives from IAEA <a href="/About/Policy/MemberStates/index.html">Member States</a> and <em>invited</em> non-Member States and organizations.</p>
								
								<p>Journalists must register through the IAEA Division of Public Information <a href="mailto:press@iaea.org">Press Office</a>. <br /><a href="/newscenter/mediaadvisory/2013/ma201321.html">More &rarr;</a></p> 
								
								<h4>Participants at General Conference</h4>
								<p>Member States participating in the General Conference. <a href="/About/Policy/GC/GC57/GC57InfDocuments/English/gc57inf-13_en.pdf">More &raquo; </a></p>
								
								<h4>Advance Information for Delegations</h4> 
                                <br />
								<p>Information about the General Conference, as well as other events organized in conjunction with the Conference's Session is available <a href="/About/Policy/GC/GC57/GC57InfDocuments/English/gc57inf-10_en.pdf">here</a>. </p> 
                                
                                <!--p>Information about the General Conference, as well as other events organized in conjunction with the Conference's Session will be added as it becomes available. </p--> 
								
								<h4>Documents</h4>
                                 <br />
								<p>The <a href="/About/Policy/GC/GC57/GC57Documents/English/gc57-1_en.pdf">Provisional Agenda</a> and a list of documents for the General Conference are posted as they become available. <a href="/About/Policy/GC/GC57/Documents/">More &rarr;</a></p>
								
								<p>For past sessions, see the <a href="/About/Policy/GC/gcarchive.html">GC Archives</a>. </p>
								
								
                                <h4>Scientific Forum at General Conference</h4>
								 <br />
                                 
<p>A Scientific Forum will be held in conjunction with the 57th General Conference  - entitled <em>The Blue Planet - Nuclear Applications for a Sustainable Marine Environment</em> from 17-18 September 2013 in Board Room D, C-Building, 4th Floor. The Forum will bring together scientists, experts and policy makers from different fields to initiate dialogue and build new partnerships and cooperation to protect and preserve the ecological balance that is vital for the survival of the coastal regions and marine environment. <a href="/About/Policy/GC/GC57/ScientificForum/">More &rarr;</a></p>
                                 
								<!--p>A Scientific Forum will be held in conjunction with the 57th General Conference  - entitled <em>The Blue Planet - Nuclear Applications for a Sustainable Marine Environment</em> - in Hall E1 in the Austria Center Vienna (ACV), which is accessible from the Vienna International Centre (VIC), the site of the General Conference. <a href="/About/Policy/GC/GC57/ScientificForum/">More &rarr;</a></p-->
                                
                                <!--p>A Scientific Forum will be held in conjunction with the 57th General Conference  - entitled <em>The Blue Planet - Nuclear Applications for a Sustainable Marine Environment</em> - in the Board Room D, C-Building, 4th Floor, the site of the General Conference, and will focus on nuclear applications related to food. <a href="/About/Policy/GC/GC57/ScientificForum/">More &rarr;</a></p-->
                                
                                
                                
                                <h4>Exhibitions</h4>
                                 <br />
                                <p>Member States and accredited organizations wishing to take part in the exhibition - usually set up as a side event to the General Conference - are kindly invited to submit their space requests by <strong>21 June 2013</strong>. </p>
                                
                                <p>Relevant information and specifications shall be made available to the prospective exhibitors in due course. It should be noted that specific stands may not be automatically reserved every year by one Member State, but will be assigned by Conference Services on a rotational basis. </p>
                                
                                <p>In planning for their exhibitions during the General Conference, Member States are kindly requested to refer to the new <em>Guidelines for Exhibitions in the Vienna International Centre (VIC)</em>, which were distributed to Permanent Missions on 29 April 2013. </p>

<p>For any additional information, please contact the  <a href="mailto:MTCD-CSS-Exhibitions.Contact-Point@iaea.org">IAEA Conference Services Section</a>.</p>
                                
                                
								
								<h4>International Nuclear Safety Group (INSAG) Forum</h4>
                                <br />
								<p>The International Nuclear Safety Group (INSAG) <!--  - entitled <em>Assessing Progress in Worldwide Nuclear Safety</em> -  --> will hold its annual forum on Monday, 16 September 2013, on the opening day of the General Conference. <a href="http://www-ns.iaea.org/meetings/insaggc13.asp?s=10&l=80">More &rarr;</a></p>
                                
                                <h4>Senior Regulators' Meeting</h4>
                                <br />
								<p>The Senior Regulators' Meeting 2013 will be held on Thursday, 19 September 2013, during the week of the 57th IAEA General Conference. The provisional programme has been prepared and circulated to interested Member States. <a href="http://www-ns.iaea.org/meetings/ns/senior-regulators.asp">More &rarr;</a></p>
								
								<h4>Live Video Streaming at General Conference</h4> 
                                 <br />
								<p>Sessions at the Plenary Hall, including the opening statements of officials and delegates, will be <!--a href="mms://streamer.a1.net/wmtencoder/Webcast/IAEA/iaea2013_1.wmv"-->streamed live</a> during the whole week of the <em>General Conference</em>. Sessions of the <em>Scientific Forum</em> will also be <!--a href="mms://streamer.a1.net/wmtencoder/Webcast/IAEA/iaea2013_2.wmv"-->live-streamed</a> beginning on Tuesday, 17 September 2013. Links to the video streaming service will be provided on the opening day. </p>
							
